                "caption": "Figure 1:(a)The confidence threshold controls decoding parallelism in MinerU-Diffusion. Compared to MinerU2.5, our method achieves up to 3.26× speedup.(b)MinerU-Diffusion maintains a strong accuracy–efficiency trade-off, achieving 2.12× speedup with 99.9% and 3.01× speedup with 98.8% relative accuracy.(c)Diffusion decoding progressively reconstructs structured text from masked tokens under visual conditioning: black tokens are confirmed, red tokens are being updated, and yellow tokens remain masked, enabling parallel generation with global consistency, in contrast to autoregressive left-to-right decoding.",
